content.description:
Let's think step-by-step. To find walking directions, we need to select 'Foot' as the mode of transportation. We are currently on the OpenStreetMap webpage http://ec2-3-128-17-139.us-east-2.compute.amazonaws.com:3000/directions#map=17/40.75749/-73.98766 with the "To" address already filled in as "Penn Station". The "From" address has the default location as Times Square. Now, we should select 'Foot' as the mode of transportation from the combobox with id [166]. Then we can click the 'Go' button to get the walking directions. 

However, my next action should be to select 'Foot' from the combobox with id [166]. In the list, the option 'Foot (OSRM)' has the id [169]. I should click on it.
